# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# governance-core self-hosting (P-0066): the autonomy layer.
#
# These root-level directories are INSTALL ARTIFACTS — pure derivatives that
# `governance-core install` regenerates from the package source. They are NOT
# committed (single repo, single agent: nothing to propagate to other clones).
# Run `governance-core install --project-root .` after a fresh clone.
#
# Leading-slash anchored: these patterns must match ONLY the repo root, never
# the package source under governance_core/ (e.g. governance_core/tools/ stays
# committed — it is the SOURCE; root /tools/ is the self-installed copy).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
/.claude/hooks/
# skills/: install-managed guide skills are ignored, but authored learned
# skills (P-0068 3a) are carved back in so lesson archival is durable.
# .usage.json is the skill-learning tracker's runtime state (P-0069) — it
# lives inside learned/ but is per-session state, not an authored skill, so
# it stays ignored.
/.claude/skills/*
!/.claude/skills/learned/
/.claude/skills/learned/.usage.json
/.claude/commands/
/.claude/agents/
/contracts/
/agent_rules/
/tools/
/knowledge/
/.governance/clauses/
# installed_files.json (P-0065 Phase 2): a manifest of the autonomy layer,
# regenerated by every install/upgrade -- a pure derivative like the layer
# it indexes, so it is not committed.
/.governance/installed_files.json
# candidate-outbox (P-0065 Phase 4): consumer-side pre-uplink staging area
# for candidate envelopes -- transient, never committed.
/.governance/candidate-outbox/

# Runtime state — in-flight proposals etc. (constitution Art.4.1: never in git;
# terminal proposals are archived to /proposals/_archive/ which IS committed).
/shared_state/

# Proposal-transition snapshots written by proposal_lib (derived audit copies
# of in-flight proposals; the durable governance record is /proposals/_archive/).
/audit/
